                  </hi>. I am a fruiterer, living at Marley, in Kent On the 5th of March I placed my cart in Covent-garden Market—my great coat was on my horse—shortly after, I missed it, and, on turning round, saw the prisoner going off with it, folding it up under his arm—I jumped off the cart, followed him, and got within four yards of him—he looked round, and dropped it—I am sure he is the man who took it—I never lost sight of him.</p>
